ClinicalTrials.gov is a registry of federally and privately supported clinical trials conducted in
the United States and around the world. ClinicalTrials.gov gives you information about a trial's
purpose, who may participate, locations, and phone numbers for more details. This information
should be used in conjunction with advice from health care professionals.  
Read more...
Find trials for a specific medical condition or other criteria in the ClinicalTrials.gov registry.
ClinicalTrials.gov currently has
77,096 trials
with locations in
169 countries.
